FT  26 JUL 94 / World News in Brief: Ulster peace initiative
Sinn Fein insisted it had not rejected the Anglo-Irish Street peace
initiative. But Downing Street said the party had again 'failed to do what
90 per cent of the people of the island of Ireland want - which is, along
with the IRA, to give up violence for good'.
Paisley to urge Ulster assembly, Page 8; Editorial comment, Page 17
